  "text": "The Kubernetes RBAC authorization implementation spans multiple critical components across the plugin and pkg directories:\n\n## RBAC Authorizer (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go)\nThe `RBACAuthorizer` struct implements the core authorization logic through its `Authorize` method. This method receives authorization requests and evaluates them against RBAC policies. The authorizer delegates rule resolution to a `RequestToRuleMapper` interface, which is implemented by `DefaultRuleResolver`.\n\n## Subject Access Evaluator (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/subject_locator.go)\nThe `SubjectAccessEvaluator` is a component that evaluates which subjects (users, groups, service accounts) are allowed to perform specific actions. It implements the `SubjectLocator` interface and provides the `AllowedSubjects` method to determine which subjects can perform an action based on role bindings and the rules they reference.\n\n## Default Rule Resolver (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go)\nThe `DefaultRuleResolver` is the core component that resolves PolicyRules for users. It implements the `AuthorizationRuleResolver` interface with three key methods:\n- `RulesFor`: Returns all rules applicable to a user in a namespace\n- `VisitRulesFor`: Iterates through rules with a visitor pattern, supporting early short-circuiting\n- `GetRoleReferenceRules`: Resolves role references from RoleBindings and ClusterRoleBindings to their actual PolicyRules\n\nThe resolver accumulates rules from both cluster-wide ClusterRoleBindings and namespace-scoped RoleBindings, gathering all applicable roles and their contained rules.\n\n## SubjectAccessReview REST Handlers\nThree REST handlers expose the authorization system to API clients:\n- `pkg/registry/authorization/subjectaccessreview/rest.go`: Cluster-scoped handler for evaluating arbitrary subjects\n- `pkg/registry/authorization/localsubjectaccessreview/rest.go`: Namespace-scoped handler for evaluating subjects within a namespace\n- `pkg/registry/authorization/selfsubjectaccessreview/rest.go`: Handler for users to check their own permissions\n\nAll handlers instantiate a `REST` struct that uses the `Authorize` method to evaluate the request and return a `SubjectAccessReviewStatus` with allowed/denied decision and reason.\n\n## Bootstrap RBAC Policies\nThree files define bootstrap RBAC policies loaded at cluster startup:\n- `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go`: Base bootstrap policy definitions\n- `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/controller_policy.go`: Policies for system controllers (node, kubelet, kube-proxy, etc.)\n- `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/namespace_policy.go`: Default namespace-scoped roles (edit, view, admin)\n\nThese are loaded through `pkg/registry/rbac/rest/storage_rbac.go` via the `PostStartHook` mechanism to establish default roles and bindings.\n\n## Escalation Prevention\nThe escalation prevention system uses multiple layers:\n\n1. **Escalation Checks** (pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go):\n   - `EscalationAllowed`: Checks if user is in system:masters group (superuser)\n   - `RoleEscalationAuthorized`: Verifies explicit authorization to escalate roles\n   - `BindingAuthorized`: Verifies user can bind a specific role reference\n\n2. **Policy-Based Storage** with escalation validation:\n   - `pkg/registry/rbac/role/policybased/storage.go`: Prevents users from creating/updating Roles with permissions they don't have\n   - `pkg/registry/rbac/rolebinding/policybased/storage.go`: Prevents privilege escalation through RoleBindings\n   - `pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrole/policybased/storage.go`: Prevents privilege escalation through ClusterRoles, including aggregation rules\n   - `pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrolebinding/policybased/storage.go`: Prevents privilege escalation through ClusterRoleBindings\n\n3. **Escalation Validation Functions**:\n   - `ConfirmNoEscalation` (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go): Validates that rules don't grant permissions beyond what the user already has\n   - `ConfirmNoEscalationInternal` (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/internal_version_adapter.go): Converts internal rbac types to v1 before validation\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\nAdditional files provide supporting functionality:\n- `pkg/registry/rbac/validation/policy_compact.go`: Compacts rules for efficient comparison\n- `pkg/registry/rbac/helpers.go`: Utility function `IsOnlyMutatingGCFields` to detect garbage collection mutations\n- `pkg/registry/rbac/rest/storage_rbac.go`: Main REST storage provider that coordinates policy-based storage for all RBAC resources\n\n## Authorization Flow\nThe complete authorization chain: RBACAuthorizer.Authorize → VisitRulesFor → DefaultRuleResolver.VisitRulesFor → GetRoleReferenceRules (to get rules from Role/ClusterRole) → RuleAllows (to match request against rules). During create/update operations, policy-based storage wrappers intercept to validate escalation rules using ConfirmNoEscalation to ensure users cannot grant themselves elevated permissions."
}

